            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W. ¶ May 8 /72 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ Immediately on receiving your last letter in which you enquired what Mr Berkeley is doing about your Fungi ¶  I wrote to him and in answer he says...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.05.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne. </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">May 8 /72</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Immediately on receiving your last letter in which you enquired what Mr Berkeley is doing about your <name key="Fungi">Fungi</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to G. Bentham, 18 March 1872 (in this edition as 72-03-18a).</p>
               </note> I wrote to him and in answer he says "The notes on the Australian <name key="Fungi">Fungi</name> are printed and I only wait for the number of the Linnean Journal to come out to return the specimens to Dr Mueller to whom indeed the greater part had already been sent once and why he sent them back again I could not quite understand. Any that remain may furnish matter for a supplementary paper."<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Berkeley (1873), Berkeley (1881).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am getting on but slowly with the <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name>. I have done about 160 species including the whole of the <name key="Phyllantheae">Phyllantheae</name> which have given me a great deal of trouble with their minute flowers — Although some of Muell. Arg.'s genera require a little modification I cannot approve of many of the changes Baillon has made.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Müller (1866), Baillon (1866) and <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Baillon (1867).</p>
               </note> I have adopted <name key="Petalostigma">Petalostigma</name>
               <name key="Phyllanthus">Phyllanthus</name> (43 or 44 sp.) <name key="Andrachne">Andrachne</name>
               <name key="Breynia">Breynia</name>
               <name key="Securinega">Securinega</name>
               <name key="Neoroepera">Neoroepera</name> (2 sp.) <name key="Actephila">Actephila</name>
               <name key="Hemicyclia">Hemicyclia</name>
               <name key="Briedelia">Briedelia</name> and <name key="Cleistanthus">Cleistanthus</name> — I cannot unite the two latter with the American &amp; African <name key="Amanoa">Amanoa</name> Baillon has too much neglected the fruits.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust now I shall soon receive the box you announce</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron F. v. Mueller</p>
